    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im working on my 2018 camry and just finished replacing the brake pads. but now when i take it out on the road i hear this really annoying high pitched squealing sound whenever i hit the brakes. not sure if its a sensor or if the caliper might be stuck or something. any idea what thats could be?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That high-pitched squeal when braking can be caused by a few things, often related to the new pads or the hardware. It might be the brake pads themselves needing a bedding-in period, or perhaps a slight contaminant on the rotors is causing the noise. It's also possible that the caliper isn't seating perfectly, leading to a slight vibration. Have you checked to ensure the anti-rattle clips or hardware wear indicators are properly installed?",
      "source": "target",
