    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An erratic, rhythmic sound during braking is more concerning than a simple squeal, suggesting something loose or catching inside the assembly. This could indicate a piece of debris, like a small shard of metal or a piece of old pad material, is trapped between the pad and rotor. It might also point to a caliper guide pin that isn't fully seated or is binding unevenly. It's best to have a mechanic inspect the caliper assembly thoroughly to rule out mechanical failure.",
      "source": "target",
